Business Brief -- Bank of Montreal:
   Plan Is Proposed to Acquire
   Rest of Nesbitt Thomson
Nesbitt employees, along with receiving Bank of Montreal
shares, would continue to hold shares in the subsidiary,
although these won't carry any voting rights. The bank's
acquisition of the minority interest is subject to the
approval of Nesbitt employees and regulatory clearance. Of
the C$75 million purchase price, about C$32 million relates
to good will, the bank said.
   Nesbitt had net income of C$22 million in the fiscal year
ended Oct. 31, up from C$5 million a year earlier. Revenue
rose to C$212 million from C$156 million.